  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "operation manager",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Liaise with clients to follow up on post-fixture matters and provide timely updates on issue resolution.</p></li><li><p>Ensure smooth, efficient, and trouble-free day-to-day site operations.</p></li><li><p>Plan and execute operational targets and objectives on both short-term and long-term bases.</p></li><li><p>Manage overseas materials sourcing, inventory planning, and coordination.</p></li><li><p>Oversee site management, including manpower deployment, work progress monitoring, and scheduling of works.</p></li><li><p>Report regularly to the Project Manager, Project Director, or Business Unit Head.</p></li><li><p>Manage procurement activities, material planning, stock control, and ensure timely delivery of equipment, building components, and related logistics throughout all stages of construction.</p></li><li><p>Drive the adoption of innovative construction methodologies and best practices on site to improve productivity and achieve lean construction outcomes.</p></li><li><p>Demonstrate sound knowledge of construction contract terms, conditions, and standard industry practices.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>5 years of relevant experience</strong> in project management and/or site management for building or construction projects.</p></li><li><p>Strong technical understanding of construction methodologies, sequencing, and site execution, with exposure to <strong>Precast and DfMA technologies</strong> being an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Proactive and solution-oriented, with the ability to plan, coordinate, and manage site resources effectively.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on team leader with the ability to make timely and well-considered decisions in fast-paced or high-pressure environments.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and coordination skills to work effectively with stakeholders across different functions.</p></li></ul>",
